s book is false). There were student protests about a lecturer from the Chemical Weapons Research Lab in Porter Down. Vice Chancellor expelled three students without a hearing. Resulted in a mass sit
-in with about 2,000 students and staff (even manual staff). Felt it was totally unjust. Very exciting. Same time as Paris student uprisings. Upheavals going on all over England \endash 
 most prominent ones at Essex and LSE. He spoke a lot at the sit-in, took the lead. Eventually suggested the creation of a Committee of Inquiry \endash 
 a way of getting the VC off the hook. As a result, the protest was called off. Students were given representation in all the major Committees. Insisted on a proper hearing system for all people accused of things. In fact the students weren\rquote 
