t believe in physical punishment. First hypothesis was that the men are domesticated on the boats while women have to do manua
l labour while men are away. Ends up with a dual skilled household. Incorrect in fact. In the West of Scotland they have a similar kind of inshore fishing but the families are patriarchal. Came to realise that the family system in Shetland was a historica
l inheritance from Norway \endash 
