ound Archive. Part of the Edwardians project, then used for the Fishermen one. Can still see him. Remember the story about the burial of the laird and how the local people weren\rquote 
t asked. Made him realise that people were remembering things which weren\rquote t ne
cessarily true, more mythical. The way he told the story related to class and religion. People who come up to the funeral, mainly from the South, start drinking. Set off on foot with the funeral to the burial ground. Drop off one by one, drunk. Finally th
